data.description: This modern Lodge Home of your dreams sits on 5.36 acres of Florida grasses, oaks and citrus. The 2329 sqft footprint spreads into outdoor spaces optimized for shade in Summer and Sun in Winter and allows you to live and entertain outdoors. 3 spacious bedrooms provide spaces for working or resting. An eat-in kitchen with a custom pantry adds functionality for your lifestyle. Rooms are lit by natural light through the many windows. Second floor rooms have a tree-house feel overlooking the green lawn. The great room extends through the beams to the 2nd story ceiling creating a vaulted expanse. Bedroom ceilings are all natural wood and beams creating a rare destination experience in your every day. This high and dry acreage is ideally suited for horses or other farm animals. There are horses or cattle on all adjacent properties. The property is fenced and cross fenced creating 5 separate sections. No water pools anywhere on this parcel. 3200 covered sq feet of workshop and/or barn space expands opportunities for crafts, hobbies or animal stalls. A raised bed garden area and chicken runs are fenced from wildlife. This home has a unique history and has been respectfully updated. It was designed and soundly built by a horticulturalist in 1984 and operated as a fruit farm for many years. The kitchen and 3 bathrooms were renovated and significant upgrades were made throughout the home and property within the last 5 years by licensed contractors. Bring your country dreams, animals and hobbies to this non-deed restricted, no HOA, dead-end neighborhood just 12 minutes from Publix and 15 minutes from downtown Lakewood Ranch. You are going to love the quiet and room to roam so close to conveniences.
